snippet.textDisplay:
A few months ago I found an inexpensive Windows tablet on Amazon by a company called NuVision.  It's working well, and runs full Windows 10.  It's a little big to be a phone (a little under 5"x8.5"), but I have no doubt its size could be reduced.  Add in what would be needed  for this thing to make and receive phone calls, and it'd be fine.  
I can't see what's slowing this down.  I'd jump at the chance to have a Windows 10 phone.
